               <p>DANIEL LYONS. I am a <rs id="t18310106-148-viclabel848" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-148-victim1321 t18310106-148-viclabel848"></join>. I lost this property from <placeName id="t18310106-148-crimeloc849">Short's-gardens, Drury-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-148-crimeloc849" type="placeName" value="Short's-gardens, Drury-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310106-148-crimeloc849" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310106-148-off846 t18310106-148-crimeloc849"></join>, where I lodge, on the 5th of January, out of the trunk, I left it safe when I went out to work - the prisoner is a stranger.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310106-148-person1322">
                  ANN 
                  LYONS
               <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1322" type="surname" value="LYONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1322" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1322" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am cousin of 
               <persName id="t18310106-148-person1323">
                  Daniel 
                  Lyons
               <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1323" type="surname" value="Lyons"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1323" type="given" value="Daniel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1323" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and live<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183101060078"></xptr>with him. On the 5th of January I was going up to his room, about two o'clock, and met the prisoner coming down stairs with the trunk in his hand - when he saw me, he drove up again; I asked what he wanted, he said a woman, named Barnes, or some name like that- I said he had no right to go up, without inquiring; he said he saw no one in the house, and he thought no one lived there - I went into my brother's room, but did not then miss the trunk; the prisoner staid about twenty minutes, and then went down - I went to the room, and missed the trunk - I screamed out, and Mr. Conner stopped the prisoner with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310106-148-person1324">
                  TIMOTHY 
                  CONNER
               <interp inst="t18310106-148-person1324" type="surname" value="CONNER"></interp>
